![Alt text](/screen02.png?raw=true "tvOS Browser Tab Switcher")

![Alt text](/screen03.png?raw=true "tvOS Browser Menu")


***tvOS Browser*** is a webbrowser for Apple TV devices running tvOS. It's using private API's, Apple does normally not allow to use this in App Store distributed apps. The latest version has some significant changes:
- It's now using WKWebView instead of UIWebView, which results in much improved performance and better website rendering.
- Added support for browser Tabs
- New modern Liquid Glass UI
- Added full screen video player, enabled by default (can be disabled in the Menu)

This project is an improved version developed with the help of AI ([Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)): the full screen video player transport controls (fast-forward, scrubbing, transport bar), the back/double-back navigation, the arrow button shortcuts, and several input-handling fixes were built in collaboration with it.

This code is provided as is with no warrenty or liability. Use at your own risk and do ***not*** distribute builds of this project on the App Store.


How to Install tvOS Browser
=============

There is ***no*** ready to use binary available on this repository. You need to install Xcode and build/run the project yourself.
To install this app, connect your Apple TV to your macOS computer via WiFi (or USB on older devices). Open this project in Xcode and install to your Apple TV.
Connecting to your Apple TV wirelessly: http://www.redmondpie.com/how-to-wirelessly-connect-apple-tv-4k-to-xcode-on-mac/.

How to Use tvOSBrowser
=============

Quick start:
- Double press on the center of the touch area of the Apple TV Remote to switch between cursor & scroll mode.
- Press the touch area while in cursor mode to click.
- Single tap the Menu button to go back. To exit the app, tap Menu (Back) twice within 2 seconds when there is no more history ("Press Back again to exit").
- Single tap the Play/Pause button to show the Quick Menu, with: input URLs, search Google, reload the page, go forward, or jump to the root page of the current site ("Go to <domain>").
- Double tap the Play/Pause button to: display the full Side Menu, with: Favorites, History, set/open homepage, change user agent, clear cache, and clear cookies and more.

Arrow buttons (clickpad edges) while browsing:
- Single press Up/Down: scroll the page vertically (Up at the top of the page moves focus to the top Navigation bar).
- Single press Left/Right: scroll the page horizontally.
- Double press Up: open the Tabs overview.
- Double press Down: open Favorites.
- Double press Left: open History.
- Double press Right: open a New Tab.

Tabs overview:
- Swipe left/right to move between tab cards, press the touch area to switch tabs.
- Swipe up (or tap Play/Pause) to close the focused tab.
- Tap Menu to close the overview.

Full screen video player (enabled by default; can be disabled in the Menu):
- Press Right repeatedly to fast-forward at 2x, 4x, 8x, 16x and up to 32x; press Left to step the speed back down.
- Press Play/Pause (or the touch area) while fast-forwarding to resume normal playback from that exact point.
- Press Left/Right while paused to skip ±10 seconds.
- Swipe on the touch area to scrub the timeline; while paused, consecutive quick swipes accelerate the scrubbing (up to 6x).
- A transport bar shows the current position, progress, and remaining time (or total duration, configurable in the Side Menu). It stays visible while paused and auto-hides during playback.
- Tap Menu to close the player.

The Side menu lets you:
- Go to Home page
- Set Home page
- Manage Favorites
- Manage History
- Show Tabs
- Open New Tab
- Hide/Show top Navigation bar
- Set page Scaling options
- Increase/decrease Font size
- Enable/disable Full Screen player
- Choose the video player time display (remaining time or total duration)
- Switch Desktop/Mobile User Agent
- Show some video diagnostics
- Clear cache
- Cleare cookies
- Show the usage guide
